Class Shark

com.example.projectfx.species.Species

com.example.projectfx.species.Shark
All Implemented Interfaces:
Movable, Reproducible, Sleepable
public class Shark extends Carnivore
The Shark class represents a carnivorous species of shark in the ecosystem. This class extends the Carnivore class and implements behaviors specific to sharks, such as hunting, attacking prey, moving swiftly in the water, and reproducing.

      public Shark(String name, int energy, Positionn positionn, Environment environment, int attackStrength, double swimSpeed, int vitesse, javafx.scene.image.ImageView imageView)
      Constructs a new Shark with the specified attributes. Sharks are powerful carnivores with a high attack strength and fast swimming speed.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the shark.
      energy - The initial energy of the shark.
      positionn - The position of the shark in the ecosystem.

      swimSpeed - The swimming speed of the shark.
      vitesse - The speed of movement.
      imageView - The image representation of the shark.
